description: {"blocks":[{"key":"376qm","text":"This protocol describes the ex vivo fast-scan cyclic voltammetry (FSCV) technique for detecting dopamine within the dorsal striatum in mice. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

funders.funder_name: Aligning Science Across Parkinson’s through the Michael J. Fox Foundation for Parkinson’s Research (MJFF)

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"15b3e","text":"Suction a single carbon fiber (7μm diameter, Goodfellow) into a capillary tube (Sutter).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8es9t","text":"Load the carbon fiber/capillary tube into a puller (Narishinge), and under the microscope, hand-cut (scalpel blade) fiber tips 30-100μm past the capillary tip.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"csuiv","text":"Anesthetize mice at postnatal day 90–110 with a ketamine-xylazine mixture. ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4obln","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fcave","text":"Perfuse the mice transcardially with ice-cold artificial cerebrospinal fluid (aCSF )containing the following (in mM): 125 NaCl, 2.5 KCl, 1.25 NaH2PO4, 2.0 CaCl2, 1.0 MgCl2, 25 NaHCO3, and 12.5 glucose, bubbled continuously with carbogen (95% O2 and 5% CO2). ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":145,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":148,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":159,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":170,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":181,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":243,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":254,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3okd9","text":"Expose the skull by a caudal to rostral midline incision and gentle remove the brain with a spatula","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bp7ns","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9rpa0","text":"Glue the brain to the stage of a vibrating microtome (Leica Instrument) and immerse it in ice cold aCSF. ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8ao3v","text":"Cut parasagittal slices containing the dorsal striatum at a thickness of 240 μm","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"13jjo","text":"Transfer the slices to a holding chamber where there are submerged in aCSF at 37 ºC ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8ihmi","text":"Recording dish with cover stimulating electrode and carbon fiber electrode, Amplifier (Molecular Devices), a digitizer (Molecular Devices), and pClamp (Molecular Devices)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4t6dq","text":"Before recording, condition the electrodes by running the ramp at 60 Hz for 15 min and 10 Hz for another 15 min. ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fegf","text":"Deliver a voltage ramp to and from 1.2 V (400 V/s) every 100 ms (10 Hz) to detect the oxidation and redox peak for DA.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"155fb","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7pkbp","text":"Before recording, calibrate the carbon fiber electrode by applying a flow of dopamine diluted in aSCF in known concentrations until dopamine signals are stable","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"g11k","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eu3st","text":"Dopamine transients are evoked by electrical stimulation delivered through a concentric, bipolar electrode (FHC) placed in the rostrodorsal striatum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d9ajv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7cfgm","text":"Perforvoltammetricic measurements by sampling at dorsostriatal sites ~200–400 µm ventral and posterior from the forceps minor corpus callosum. ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8kc90","text":"Take four recordings each site with two-minute intervals between recordings and then averaged as a reported measure.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6qjl3","text":"The voltammogram and peak oxidative current amplitudes of the dopamine transient are measured. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4qa6","text":"Note: Experiments were rejected when the evoked current did not have the characteristic electrochemical signature of dopamine.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":126}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5v63u","text":"-Four recordings taken at each site with two-minute intervals between recordings and then averaged as a reported measure.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"h38s","text":"-Considering the slice where the GPe was first evidenced as the most lateral slice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":83}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a762v","text":"consecutive slices 480 µm apart and medial of this lateral slice should be considered intermediate and medial ones.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":115}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9bqui","text":"-The recording order of the slices is randomized to reduce potential recording biases and mitigate possible electrode sensitivity issues. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b1nmb","text":"-Electrode sensitivity is to be retested at the end of recordings with a freshly made dopamine stock used for calibration. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"h7fq","text":"-Recordings from electrodes with a larger than 10% change from calibrated dopamine solution are subtracted. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

title: Fast scan cyclic voltammetry
